<br>
However, if that is what some chanters want to do to earn money instead of farming some boring items, its fine with me. im just not that kind of player.<br>
<br>
However sometime after a raid, i just run to Nexus (or a newbie zone) and shout &quot;Free C3 for all&quot; or something like that, and normally end up casting on 80-90 people before i leave..guess people tell their friends to hurry there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Some people still try to donate, but i reject it all, because i got the spell for free from Guild, so i dont have to earn money to cover my initial investment or anything like that. (i understand fully that some people try to at least get enough money to cover spell cost)<br>
<br>
Of course other chanters in the zone sometimes send me mad tells because i ruin their market, but hey, i do it because i like to make people happy, and its my choice to spend my time doing it.<br>
<br>
Only thing i ask of my &quot;customers&quot; is that they need to respect that i do not cast C3 unless i am offering it to them, or are sitting in Nexus/bazaar etc.<br>
<br>
And they actually respect that..they dont send me lots of tells in the middle of raids etc, so i guess they do a /who all before sending the tell.<br>
<br>
The added bonus is ofcourse that i never have to pay for ports/rezzes/etc since people remember me, even looong time after i casted it on them.<br>
<br>
Sometimes i also run into the lvl 60 super-twink-with-2-days-played-time who demand C3 now, but most of the time i think people are friendly and really appreciate it.<br>
<br>
I dont do this because im rich, actually i only have a few kpp in bank <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
My favorite thing is casting on newbies who actually still wear cloth armor etc, and who dont even know the buff name.<br>
It so fun to get a tell after a few minutes from a player who is astonished by his mana regen or haste etc, and ask me if im a god or GM or so. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Then again some chanters think i spoil the newbie players, but /shrug<br>
<br>
Hmmmm i seem to be rambling, but just wanted to add that not all chanters are greedy, i know quite a few who act like me.<br>
